defaultThe first item the Pressure Group wishes to address is the continual reference to the idea that people who complain about the Ombudsman service consist largely of those who have not had an investigation and are thereby aggrieved by this single fact.
default&#xa0;
default Let us assure you that this is not the case.
default&#xa0;
default Approximately 50% of our Pressure Group have received some form of investigation from the Ombudsman, yet they are still dissatisfied. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultIf individuals are dissatisfied 
defaultfollowing an investigationdefault, then the 
default‘quality’default of those investigations is suspect.
default&#xa0;
default 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;defaultThe main reason for our dissatisfaction is the systematic manipulation and denial of the facts by PHSO in order to find no case to answer or minimize the case against the public body concerned and their total lack of accountability when their poor decision making is criticised.default&#xa0;default default&#xa0;defaultIn 2010 – 2011
default&#xa0;
default PHSO found in favour of 1.45% of complainants.
default&#xa0;
default In 2011 – 2012 PHSO found in favour of 1.4% of complaints, therefore it is unsurprising that 64% of the public expressed the view that making a complaint would not make a difference. They were right. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThere is little point using resources to encourage more people to make a complaint when the Ombudsman service is clearly unable to deliver justice and remedy to the vast majority of those who already do. 
default&#xa0;
defaultWe would like to share some information with the Committee to supplement the answers given by Dame Julie Mellor and provide a more complete picture.
default&#xa0;
default We would appreciate some feedback from the Committee on the points we raise.
